Sure! To write an if/then statement in C programming language, you can use the following syntax:

if (condition) {
    // Code to execute if the condition is true
}

For example, if you want to check if a variable named "age" is greater than 18, you can write the following code:

if (age > 18) {
    printf("You are eligible to vote.");
}

This code will print "You are eligible to vote." if the value of the "age" variable is greater than 18.
